        <article>
            <h2>My Favourite Hikes in Sydney</h2>

        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/5dVz7WWV7eK2" target="_blank">Dalpura Canyon</a> – A quiet, off-the-beaten-path canyon in the Blue Mountains with stunning rock formations and crystal-clear pools.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/j1Z7ZJJqAPs" target="_blank">Porters Pass</a> – A scenic loop near Blackheath with waterfalls, lush rainforest, and dramatic cliffs.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/xqYPBPcJ8Ww" target="_blank">Taronga to Spit Bridge</a> – A coastal walk with harbor views, secluded beaches, and plenty of spots to stop and swim.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/GkP5eH6AvCr" target="_blank">Grand Canyon, Blue Mountains</a> – One of the most beautiful hikes in the Blue Mountains, with lush greenery, rock overhangs, and narrow canyons.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/WAVq3fM8p7n" target="_blank">Wolli Creek National Park</a> – A hidden bushwalk close to the city, with quiet trails, sandstone cliffs, and native wildlife.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/Z5u7dXox4Jt" target="_blank">Macquarie Pass National Park</a> – A rainforest escape south of Sydney with waterfalls, creek crossings, and a bit of rock scrambling.</li>
            <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/Ni2f6ZWpHxu" target="_blank">Karloo Pools</a> – A short but rewarding hike in the Royal National Park, leading to deep, clear swimming holes perfect for a summer day.</li>
        </ul>
